==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Granulose
<hw>Gran"u*lose`</hw> <pr>(gr⟦acr⟧n"⟦usl⟧*l⟦omac⟧s`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[From <er>Granule</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>The
main constituent of the starch grain or granule, in distinction from the
framework of cellulose. Unlike cellulose, it is colored blue by iodine,
and is converted into dextrin and sugar by boiling acids and amylolytic
ferments.</def> <mark>[Obsolescent]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>granulose</ent>⟦br⟧

